		<td class="alt2">
			<hr />
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Goladus</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Also I have a question, though this has probably been answered elsewhere and I just haven't seen it-- how does zoning/etc work?  Are there noticeable load times while playing?  To what extent does zoning mechanics affect play?<br />
<br />
(btw, Whiz, I liked the way you addressed the concerns about graphics ;) )</div>
			
			<hr />
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div> <br />
There are no zones in WoW unless you enter an instanced dungeon or go to Kalimdor from Azeroth on the other side of the world (both continents are on different servers, seperate from instanced dungeons). Zoning has never taken longer than ten seconds when entering a dungeon. But other than that, you can run anywhere you wish without zoning -- I can run from the dwarven newbie lands all the way over to the undead newbie lands without zoning. Might get killed pretty badly in the process, but I still wouldn't zone. ;)<br />
<br />
And regardless of that, whenever the server crashed (as is expected in any alpha), it was never a painful process to log back on the game. I was impressed with the load time (a fraction of the time it takes to log on to EQ).</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
